# spec 25 §6 AC-4: `a2a feedback status` reads the consumer-local ledger
# (.a2a/feedback/ledger.yaml). An empty/absent ledger is a friendly, exit-0
# no-op (not an error). `--json` on an empty ledger is the same friendly exit-0.
#
# The populated-ledger path resolves each item's hub-side status/resolution
# over the network (raw.githubusercontent.com) in the real binary, so the
# "unreachable hub degrades to unknown, exit 0" branch is covered by
# internal/feedback/status_test.go's httptest server — NOT here: this txtar
# stays strictly network-free per the T3 isolation invariant.

# no ledger at all -> friendly, exit 0
exec a2a feedback status
stdout 'no feedback filed'

# --json on an empty ledger -> same friendly exit-0 (the empty short-circuit
# precedes the json branch), still exit 0
exec a2a feedback status --json
stdout 'no feedback filed'
